collectionMetadata.name: Combined And Gross Enrolment Ratio For Primary, Secondary & Tertiary Education
collectionMetadata.description:
- Total number of students enrolled in a given level of education regardless of age expressed as a percentage of population in the theoretical age group for that level of education
- Refers to resident population, i.e. Singapore citizens and permanent residents.
- From 2005, the gross enrolment ratios include private education institutions.
- From 2010, the gross enrolment ratios are adjusted for residents who are based overseas and cannot be enrolled in Singapore.
- Year 1 Diploma courses are classified as post-secondary non-tertiary under ISCED 2011 from 2016 onwards.

datasetMetadata.name: Combined And Gross Enrolment Ratio For Primary, Secondary & Tertiary Education
